  <generalInformation><![CDATA[<p>With over 400 kilometres of slopes, the Four Vallées has an area for everyone. For first time skiers and boarders, Nendaz is an excellent choice with three beginner areas designed to help build confidence. Once progression has been made there are plenty of gentle slopes in and around the Printse Section linking Nendaz, Veysonnaz and Thyon. </p>
<p>Intermediate skiers have the area at their fingertips, choose from the sunny slopes in Savoleyres and La Tzoumaz or race down the highest point in Mont Fort - a challenging and often mogulled black run. For some tree lined, skiing Bruson is a quaint and quiet area just off of Verbier.  If you are after a challenge head down the marked off piste routes from Chassoure-Tortin and Monte Gelé - tackle the moguls and relatively steep descents. </p>]]></generalInformation>
