  <listingDescription><![CDATA[<p>The Four Vallées is Switzerlands largest interlinked ski area, giving you access to over 400 kilometres of slopes across six resorts covered on one ski pass. It is renowned for its challenging runs around the Mont Fort area, however there is plenty of opportunities for beginners and intermediates. The local slopes of Nendaz are great for those just starting out and the wider Printze sector is perfect for intermediates, experts should head out and explore the steeper runs of Verbier where there are set ski off piste itineraries.</p>
<p> </p>
